cs.OS, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.PL

This paper discusses OS-level virtualization and its implementation on the Windows platform, which falls under the category of operating systems (cs.OS). It also addresses the challenges of virtualizing Windows system services, which involves security and fault tolerance, making it relevant to the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the virtualization of different services, including web servers and database servers, which relates to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper describes a general technique for virtualizing services, which involves programming languages and compilers (cs.PL).
